\begin{eqnarray}
{\cal B}(\Lambda_c^+ \to p K^- \pi^+)_{\rm CLEO}=(5.0\pm0.5\pm1.2)\%. \label{eq:cleo_pKpi}
\end{eqnarray} 
Based on the large amount of data, Belle collaboration   also started to study  the doubly Cabibbo-suppressed processes~\cite{Yang:2015ytm}.   Making use of the data collected  in the $e^+e^-$ collision at the center-of-mass energy of $\sqrt s=4.599$ GeV and adopting  the double-tag technique, BES-III  collaboration has reported  first measurements of absolute hadronic branching fractions of  Cabibbo-favored decay modes~\cite{Ablikim:2015flg}. In total, twelve $\Lambda_c$ decay modes were observed  with the significant improvement on the branching fraction in particular for the $\Lambda_c\to pK^-\pi^+$:
\begin{eqnarray} 
